WEBVTT

1
00:00:41.180 --> 00:00:44.140
(On January 8. 2004. there was a disappearance)

2
00:00:44.260 --> 00:00:46.970
(A woman whose online name was "Hasumi")

3
00:00:47.100 --> 00:00:50.100
(Based on anonymous discussion in the forum "2 Channel")

4
00:00:50.230 --> 00:00:53.900
(This work has been adapted from the actual published content)

5
00:02:23.650 --> 00:02:28.490
Title: Kisaragi Station

6
00:02:28.620 --> 00:02:33.790
("Kisaragi Station." a modern-day spirit station)

7
00:02:40.090 --> 00:02:43.550
(The door is about to close. All passengers please pay attention)

8
00:02:45.930 --> 00:02:48.140
(Shin Hamamatsu Station)

9
00:04:14.240 --> 00:04:20.030
(Hayama)

10
00:04:28.240 --> 00:04:31.030
- Think about the next part
- OK

11
00:04:31.240 --> 00:04:32.780
-See you later
-Bye

12
00:04:38.120 --> 00:04:40.790
Are you here for an interview?
Please come in

13
00:04:41.120 --> 00:04:42.290
Excuse me

14
00:05:16.120 --> 00:05:17.510
(Hibayama Disappearance)
(Girl's Disappearance in May)

15
00:05:17.540 --> 00:05:18.930
(Soshi-Cho Case Witness)
(Will Mystery Information Affect the Case?)

16
00:05:18.950 --> 00:05:22.330
(Sudden Disappearance at Sanki Pass)

17
00:05:26.300 --> 00:05:28.710
Sorry for keeping you waiting

18
00:05:38.100 --> 00:05:41.480
Nice to meet you. I'm Haruna Tsutsumi

19
00:05:42.600 --> 00:05:44.610
I'm Sumiko Hayama

20
00:05:46.820 --> 00:05:48.530
I said in the message
you didn't need to bring anything...

21
00:05:48.650 --> 00:05:54.780
Thank you very much for taking time out of your busy schedule to accept the interview today

22
00:05:54.820 --> 00:05:56.790
Rin. quickly leave the room

23
00:05:57.910 --> 00:05:58.700
OK

24
00:06:00.750 --> 00:06:02.280
Please sit down

25
00:06:02.410 --> 00:06:04.580
Thank you

26
00:06:06.710 --> 00:06:08.440
Is that your daughter?

27
00:06:08.460 --> 00:06:10.610
No it's my niece

28
00:06:11.170 --> 00:06:13.800
There is a private high school near here

29
00:06:13.970 --> 00:06:16.950
I helped my brother by taking care
of her while she was in school

30
00:06:17.800 --> 00:06:19.420
You guys have such a good relationship

31
00:06:20.350 --> 00:06:23.260
Miss Tsutsumi. you are a college student. right?

32
00:06:23.350 --> 00:06:26.000
Yes. I major in Ethnology (Anthropology)

33
00:06:26.020 --> 00:06:29.230
My graduation thesis is on "Mysterious Disappearances"

34
00:06:29.360 --> 00:06:32.650
Because I always feel it has a kind of deja vu feeling

35
00:06:32.860 --> 00:06:36.240
That's why you want to visit me?

36
00:06:36.870 --> 00:06:41.680
I want to write new content that no one has seen

37
00:06:41.790 --> 00:06:43.540
There are many people like you

38
00:06:43.910 --> 00:06:47.350
But a lot of people are not serious

39
00:06:47.380 --> 00:06:49.090
and don't believe me at all

40
00:06:49.210 --> 00:06:51.170
But. I...

41
00:06:51.260 --> 00:06:56.190
No problem. we sent so many messages
to each other

42
00:06:56.260 --> 00:06:59.300
Miss Tsutsumi. you are someone
I can trust

43
00:07:11.400 --> 00:07:13.770
Ms Hayama

44
00:07:15.320 --> 00:07:17.380
I hope you tell me

45
00:07:18.820 --> 00:07:23.790
about January 8. 2004

46
00:07:25.870 --> 00:07:31.080
You went to another world

47
00:07:42.010 --> 00:07:45.230
{\an8}(I got off work very late that day)

48
00:07:45.350 --> 00:07:47.689
{\an8}(Took the last train home)

49
00:07:45.350 --> 00:07:53.530
(August 23. 2004. 11:40pm)

50
00:07:47.690 --> 00:07:53.730
{\an8}(I asked my brother to pick me up
at Saginomiya Station)

51
00:08:43.780 --> 00:08:47.200
{\an8}(The Enshu Railway should have
no tunnels)

52
00:08:47.290 --> 00:08:51.900
{\an8}(But the train suddenly entered
a tunnel)

53
00:09:12.400 --> 00:09:14.160
[no signal]

54
00:09:12.400 --> 00:09:14.160
{\an8}(then...)

55
00:09:14.190 --> 00:09:16.550
{\an8}(I don't know what happened)

56
00:09:16.860 --> 00:09:18.000
{\an8}(I noticed...)

57
00:09:18.030 --> 00:09:20.940
{\an8}(...the train going to some place)

58
00:09:25.450 --> 00:09:29.330
{\an8}(There was a salaryman in the train)

59
00:09:32.170 --> 00:09:34.250
{\an8}(along with three young men and women)

60
00:09:35.790 --> 00:09:40.970
{\an8}(and a high school girl...
all five are sleeping)

61
00:09:44.090 --> 00:09:50.850
{\an8}(The curtains on the operator's room were closed. so you can't see inside)

62
00:09:56.570 --> 00:10:00.810
Hey. wake up. you are a Sea Beach High School student. right?

63
00:10:00.820 --> 00:10:04.860
Hey! Wake up!

64
00:10:08.410 --> 00:10:10.450
Excuse me

65
00:10:10.620 --> 00:10:12.580
Huh?

66
00:10:14.830 --> 00:10:17.340
Where is this?

67
00:10:17.540 --> 00:10:19.800
I over-slept

68
00:10:20.170 --> 00:10:22.590
Where is this?

69
00:10:23.970 --> 00:10:26.070
Daisuke. where is this place? Hurry and check!

70
00:10:26.090 --> 00:10:26.880
No signal?

71
00:10:26.890 --> 00:10:31.480
{\an8}(Everyone woke up confused
by the situation)

72
00:10:31.600 --> 00:10:35.190
{\an8}(then the train arrived at a station)

73
00:10:37.650 --> 00:10:39.020
We arrived

74
00:10:40.360 --> 00:10:41.400
What are you doing?

75
00:10:41.530 --> 00:10:43.400
Where is this?

76
00:10:43.530 --> 00:10:44.320
Ah. the door is opening

77
00:10:44.450 --> 00:10:46.660
(Kisaragi Station)

78
00:10:46.780 --> 00:10:49.020
Kisaragi Station…

79
00:10:49.910 --> 00:10:52.080
Did you get out of the train then?

80
00:10:52.660 --> 00:10:55.210
Everyone just thought it was a sitting station

81
00:10:55.830 --> 00:10:56.500
but…

82
00:10:56.630 --> 00:10:59.920
I've never heard of that name

83
00:11:07.390 --> 00:11:09.970
[No signal]
Still not working...

84
00:11:10.100 --> 00:11:11.270
Where is this?

85
00:11:11.390 --> 00:11:13.060
Where is Kisaragi? Never heard of it

86
00:11:13.770 --> 00:11:15.480
You should wake me up

87
00:11:15.730 --> 00:11:16.650
Sorry

88
00:11:17.100 --> 00:11:19.060
Wait. can't we go back?

89
00:11:19.270 --> 00:11:21.320
Hey. is there no train?

90
00:11:22.650 --> 00:11:24.940
I'm asking you

91
00:11:24.950 --> 00:11:26.860
I do not know

92
00:11:27.490 --> 00:11:28.660
Useless

93
00:11:35.500 --> 00:11:39.140
Well. do you know where the toilet is?

94
00:11:39.210 --> 00:11:40.840
I don't know…

95
00:11:42.880 --> 00:11:44.810
Isn't this weird?

96
00:11:49.300 --> 00:11:51.510
How are you doing?

97
00:11:52.010 --> 00:11:55.480
Well. I was supposed to get off at Saginomiya

98
00:11:55.600 --> 00:11:57.820
Is there a train I can take back?

99
00:11:57.850 --> 00:12:01.690
Sorry i don't know either

100
00:12:07.740 --> 00:12:10.030
what happened?

101
00:12:10.990 --> 00:12:14.300
That wall...

102
00:12:14.330 --> 00:12:16.120
Huh? Wall?

103
00:12:24.920 --> 00:12:27.590
Seems like nothing special...

104
00:12:27.930 --> 00:12:30.890
Sorry. it must be my imagination

105
00:12:32.680 --> 00:12:34.890
Looking at your uniform. you must be from
Sea Beach High School. right?

106
00:12:35.020 --> 00:12:36.560
Do you know me?

107
00:12:38.690 --> 00:12:40.230
I don't know.

108
00:12:42.150 --> 00:12:44.400
I am a teacher at that school

109
00:12:44.530 --> 00:12:46.150
Huh? Is that right?

110
00:12:46.280 --> 00:12:48.490
I've only been there for a year

111
00:12:48.610 --> 00:12:51.200
Some students don't know me

112
00:12:50.660 --> 00:12:51.740
Excuse me

113
00:12:53.160 --> 00:12:54.330
My name is Sumiko Hayama

114
00:12:54.450 --> 00:12:57.160
I'm the head teacher of Class 1. Please to meet you.

115
00:12:57.660 --> 00:13:00.250
I am Asuka Miyazaki in Class 3

116
00:13:02.710 --> 00:13:03.790
Hey

117
00:13:06.550 --> 00:13:09.880
If the train comes. wake me up

118
00:13:11.890 --> 00:13:13.050
Excuse me

119
00:13:18.390 --> 00:13:19.430
Hey!

120
00:13:23.810 --> 00:13:25.570
Did you order me around just now?

121
00:13:25.730 --> 00:13:27.900
Are you ordering me?

122
00:13:28.740 --> 00:13:29.780
i am not ordering you

123
00:13:29.900 --> 00:13:31.200
What do you mean?

124
00:13:31.490 --> 00:13:32.880
Maybe a train will come

125
00:13:32.910 --> 00:13:34.870
Better to wait at the station...

126
00:13:39.080 --> 00:13:42.860
Let's go. I'm thirsty

127
00:13:47.500 --> 00:13:50.130
Are you OK?

128
00:13:50.300 --> 00:13:52.380
Sorry

129
00:13:53.550 --> 00:13:59.370
Later. I also left the station with that Miyazaki student

130
00:13:59.390 --> 00:14:02.800
Looking for other means of transportation

131
00:14:02.810 --> 00:14:07.020
But there are only houses near the station

132
00:14:07.360 --> 00:14:09.780
But those houses...

133
00:14:11.610 --> 00:14:16.320
It feels like no one lives in any of them

134
00:14:16.580 --> 00:14:19.450
Excuse me. is anyone there?

135
00:14:20.250 --> 00:14:21.620
Excuse me!

136
00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:25.710
Teacher. there is no one here

137
00:14:26.080 --> 00:14:29.340
Don't you think it's weird? No one at all

138
00:14:29.550 --> 00:14:31.590
Let's look again

139
00:14:41.480 --> 00:14:42.640
Come on. Miki!

140
00:14:49.270 --> 00:14:50.360
Get out of the way

141
00:14:51.940 --> 00:14:54.490
Shota. wait for me...!

142
00:14:57.820 --> 00:14:59.790
Teacher. are you okay?

143
00:15:01.700 --> 00:15:03.040
I'm fine

144
00:15:15.590 --> 00:15:18.350
I don't know what's wrong. We should go back

145
00:15:24.890 --> 00:15:28.770
What is that? What is it. damn it!

146
00:15:29.400 --> 00:15:31.900
Daisuke...

147
00:15:32.230 --> 00:15:34.320
Really. it's noisy

148
00:15:36.240 --> 00:15:38.700
Excuse me... what's wrong...

149
00:15:39.740 --> 00:15:42.450
Don't know. but Daisuke...

150
00:15:42.580 --> 00:15:45.620
I want to go home.. I want to go home

151
00:15:46.620 --> 00:15:47.710
Let's go

152
00:15:52.460 --> 00:15:54.090
Hey... where are you going?

153
00:15:54.210 --> 00:15:55.550
Walking to the next station

154
00:15:55.920 --> 00:15:58.260
Don't be stupid. just wait here...

155
00:15:58.390 --> 00:16:00.180
How can I stay in this kind of place!

156
00:16:00.890 --> 00:16:04.520
Hey you... please explain

157
00:16:04.810 --> 00:16:06.230
Where is your friend?

158
00:16:06.850 --> 00:16:07.940
What's that?

159
00:16:10.270 --> 00:16:12.730
That's Daisuke's voice

160
00:16:13.030 --> 00:16:15.570
I'm done here!

161
00:16:17.700 --> 00:16:18.910
Let's go

162
00:16:26.250 --> 00:16:27.660
So stupid

163
00:16:30.710 --> 00:16:32.840
Better not stay here too long

164
00:16:35.380 --> 00:16:37.010
We are leaving too

165
00:16:38.010 --> 00:16:39.930
Do you believe what those people say?

166
00:16:40.140 --> 00:16:42.850
There's no one around here

167
00:16:44.430 --> 00:16:46.230
Obviously there are so many houses

168
00:16:46.350 --> 00:16:47.770
Don't you think it's weird?

169
00:16:48.230 --> 00:16:49.230
Let's go

170
00:16:54.190 --> 00:16:57.950
Wait... Are you really leaving?

171
00:17:03.450 --> 00:17:05.830
Do you really want to go?

172
00:17:11.920 --> 00:17:16.380
{\an8}(then we walked for hours)

173
00:17:24.890 --> 00:17:25.930
Wait!

174
00:17:29.060 --> 00:17:30.140
What are you doing?

175
00:17:30.270 --> 00:17:33.810
Please tell me what happened?

176
00:17:33.940 --> 00:17:35.480
You won't believe me if I tell you

177
00:17:37.320 --> 00:17:38.570
Say it!

178
00:17:39.530 --> 00:17:41.910
We can't figure it out

179
00:17:42.490 --> 00:17:43.780
We were looking for a convenience store

180
00:17:43.910 --> 00:17:46.410
But Daisuke suddenly told us to go back quickly

181
00:17:46.870 --> 00:17:49.000
That guy never orders me around

182
00:17:49.120 --> 00:17:51.000
I was so upset. I pushed him around

183
00:17:52.790 --> 00:17:53.960
and left him there

184
00:17:54.210 --> 00:17:57.880
Then. Daisuke suddenly yelled for help. I was very scared

185
00:17:58.010 --> 00:18:01.340
No way. he turned into something like that

186
00:18:02.180 --> 00:18:03.590
Turned into what?

187
00:18:04.390 --> 00:18:07.640
He's covered in what looks like blood vessels

188
00:18:07.970 --> 00:18:11.190
I don't know. we just wanted to escape

189
00:18:17.730 --> 00:18:20.940
It's Daisuke... Shota. what should I do?

190
00:18:21.360 --> 00:18:22.740
-How should I know!
-You take it!

191
00:18:22.860 --> 00:18:24.870
Why should I answer your phone?

192
00:18:32.040 --> 00:18:34.880
(Calling. Daisuke)

193
00:18:36.130 --> 00:18:40.050
Hey? Mr. Daisuke. are you okay? Daisuke?

194
00:18:42.930 --> 00:18:43.800
Daisuke...

195
00:18:43.930 --> 00:18:45.390
What is going on?

196
00:18:50.270 --> 00:18:52.640
I heard a sound like some festival

197
00:18:52.770 --> 00:18:54.810
just to tell you

198
00:18:56.810 --> 00:18:58.570
Listen. that sound

199
00:19:01.400 --> 00:19:02.780
Taiko drum?

200
00:19:02.900 --> 00:19:04.700
Does anyone live out here?

201
00:19:05.820 --> 00:19:06.990
Shota. this...

202
00:19:07.120 --> 00:19:10.330
When Daisuke was attacked. this taiko...

203
00:19:10.950 --> 00:19:11.950
Go!

204
00:19:13.460 --> 00:19:14.750
Run

205
00:19:16.670 --> 00:19:19.880
Wait. why? Maybe we can ask for help

206
00:19:26.180 --> 00:19:28.010
What... What is going on?

207
00:19:28.140 --> 00:19:30.220
-Wait... wait...
-Run away... let's go!

208
00:19:44.360 --> 00:19:47.320
I can't do it. Shota. take a break

209
00:19:48.200 --> 00:19:50.450
If I keep running. I'll be exhausted

210
00:19:50.580 --> 00:19:51.450
Hey. stand up!

211
00:19:51.580 --> 00:19:53.040
Otherwise. you go first

212
00:19:53.870 --> 00:19:54.660
This…

213
00:19:54.790 --> 00:19:57.250
Are you afraid of going alone?

214
00:19:58.000 --> 00:19:59.040
What…

215
00:19:59.170 --> 00:20:00.540
Let's rest together

216
00:20:00.670 --> 00:20:02.050
What are you so arrogant about!

217
00:20:02.170 --> 00:20:03.760
Stop that

218
00:20:07.720 --> 00:20:10.180
Who are you ordering around? Goddamn

219
00:20:13.720 --> 00:20:14.770
Stop

220
00:20:15.100 --> 00:20:17.640
I said don't order me around

221
00:20:19.650 --> 00:20:21.400
Hey!

222
00:20:21.610 --> 00:20:25.490
It's too dangerous to walk on the rails

223
00:20:25.610 --> 00:20:27.610
What? Where are they?

224
00:20:27.860 --> 00:20:29.110
Shota. there

225
00:20:31.070 --> 00:20:32.950
Hello!

226
00:20:33.410 --> 00:20:37.830
It's too dangerous to walk on the rails!

227
00:20:37.960 --> 00:20:39.290
Some guy

228
00:20:40.210 --> 00:20:42.130
Hey!

229
00:20:42.670 --> 00:20:46.880
It's too dangerous to walk on the rails!

230
00:20:47.010 --> 00:20:48.340
Who is this guy?

231
00:20:53.010 --> 00:20:54.970
-He disappeared
-Disappeared. where did he go?

232
00:20:55.100 --> 00:20:57.060
Hey…

233
00:20:57.940 --> 00:21:02.980
-It's too dangerous to walk on the rails
-What's the matter?

234
00:21:13.950 --> 00:21:15.120
Help me

235
00:21:15.240 --> 00:21:17.080
-Let me go!
-Daisuke...

236
00:21:17.580 --> 00:21:19.620
-Let me go
-Save me

237
00:21:19.750 --> 00:21:21.210
Stay away

238
00:21:22.170 --> 00:21:24.710
-Daisuke. let go!
-Help me…

239
00:21:24.840 --> 00:21:27.260
Shota...help me...

240
00:21:27.380 --> 00:21:28.340
Shota...

241
00:21:33.600 --> 00:21:34.680
Miki?

242
00:21:37.770 --> 00:21:38.890
Daisuke...

243
00:21:48.900 --> 00:21:52.490
You guys want to leave me alone here. right?

244
00:21:53.410 --> 00:21:55.580
No I just...

245
00:21:56.620 --> 00:21:59.370
I got a...

246
00:21:59.500 --> 00:22:01.420
...way to survive here

247
00:22:02.880 --> 00:22:05.130
Just offer a living sacrifice

248
00:22:05.420 --> 00:22:08.420
That way. you won't be able to hear that sound for a while. right?

249
00:22:08.550 --> 00:22:10.260
What are you saying? How is that possible?

250
00:22:10.380 --> 00:22:14.300
OK. so who do we pick next?

251
00:22:16.010 --> 00:22:18.810
Teacher... let's go

252
00:22:20.230 --> 00:22:21.730
You go first!

253
00:22:22.770 --> 00:22:24.060
Teacher!

254
00:22:28.150 --> 00:22:29.360
I…

255
00:22:31.110 --> 00:22:32.490
Bring it on!

256
00:22:32.610 --> 00:22:33.990
very good

257
00:22:34.320 --> 00:22:35.780
It's you first!

258
00:22:38.160 --> 00:22:39.450
Teacher!

259
00:22:53.720 --> 00:22:54.970
Teacher!

260
00:22:55.930 --> 00:22:57.140
Go now

261
00:22:57.260 --> 00:22:58.890
I can't spare you!

262
00:23:02.980 --> 00:23:04.690
Teacher. hurry up

263
00:23:12.440 --> 00:23:14.360
Teacher. ahead

264
00:23:15.030 --> 00:23:16.110
Tunnel?

265
00:23:20.160 --> 00:23:23.080
Isakinu Tunnel?

266
00:23:25.080 --> 00:23:28.210
(Isakinu Tunnel)

267
00:23:29.250 --> 00:23:30.300
Let's go

268
00:24:01.450 --> 00:24:02.700
Teacher!

269
00:24:03.410 --> 00:24:06.620
Teacher! Are you all right?

270
00:24:14.170 --> 00:24:17.050
-You go first. I'm fine
-But...

271
00:24:18.260 --> 00:24:19.390
Go!

272
00:24:49.290 --> 00:24:51.500
Stop…!

273
00:25:03.760 --> 00:25:06.930
I can't spare you...!

274
00:25:21.990 --> 00:25:26.290
You don't have to be a living sacrifice
anymore. I'm going to kill you!

275
00:25:39.970 --> 00:25:41.340
Teacher. are you okay?

276
00:25:41.840 --> 00:25:44.140
Miyazaki-san... how do you...

277
00:25:45.260 --> 00:25:46.560
Miyazaki-san!

278
00:25:51.060 --> 00:25:54.690
If you want to die first.
I will fulfill your wish. die!

279
00:25:54.820 --> 00:25:56.070
